==Trivia==
*Phil Coulson was named after {{WPS|Danny Coulson}}.<ref>[https://youtu.be/K2ZZyHfNE7M?t=55 FBI Hostage Rescue Team founder Danny Coulson Part 1, Ep. 87]</ref>
*Due to the popularity of the character, Coulson was introduced into the main Marvel Comics universe.
**[[Clark Gregg]] also voices Phil Coulson in the TV series ''{{WPS|Ultimate Spider-Man}}'', where Coulson is drawn in Clark Gregg's likeness.
**Coulson appears in ''[[w:c:marvel:Avengers: Earth's Mightiest Heroes Adventures Vol 1 1|The Avengers: Earth's Mightiest Heroes Adventures #1]]'' comic book tie in to the TV series, ''{{WPS|The Avengers: Earth's Mightiest Heroes}}''.
*During a flashback to his time in Tahiti, Coulson used the question ''"Did I fall asleep?"'' to which his masseuse replied "For a little while." This was a programmed response used in Joss Whedon's TV show ''{{WPS|Dollhouse (TV series)|Dollhouse}}'' whenever one of the characters was being brainwashed.
*With appearances in ''[[Iron Man (film)|Iron Man]]'', ''[[Iron Man 2]]'', ''[[Thor (film)|Thor]]'', ''[[The Consultant]]'', ''[[A Funny Thing Happened on the Way to Thor's Hammer]]'', ''[[The Avengers]]'', over a hundred episodes of ''[[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'', one episode of ''[[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.: Slingshot]]'', ''[[Captain Marvel (film)|Captain Marvel]]'', and several  [[Comics|tie-in comics]] titles, Phil Coulson is the most featured character in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]].
*Coulson has killed four major ''[[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'' antagonists: [[John Garrett]], [[Daniel Whitehall]], [[Grant Ward]], and [[Aida]]. Conversely, he never encountered two other major ''Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.'' antagonists who were active before his death: [[Jiaying]] and [[Kasius/Destroyed Earth|Kasius]].
*Coulson was a fan of the ''{{WPS|Star Wars}}'' franchise and ''{{WPS|Call of Duty}}''.
**Coulson has his hand cut off, as a reference to ''{{WPS|The Empire Strikes Back}}''. Every movie and television show featured in [[Phase Two]] has this reference in some form.
*Coulson is one of only three humans to survive physical contact with [[Diviner]] metal, the others being [[Isabelle Hartley]] and [[Absorbing Man]]. Of these three, he is the only one who did not touch an actual Diviner but rather a contaminated [[Terrigen Crystals|Terrigen Crystal]].
*When discussing with [[Melinda May]] about a contingency plan in case he went insane like Garrett, he mentioned that he likes kangaroos.

==Behind the Scenes==
*In the films of the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]], Agent Coulson is generally depicted as a supporting character of the protagonists and used to represent [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'s presence in the plots of the films, to the point that [[Clark Gregg]] has described Coulson as ''"'''the''' S.H.I.E.L.D. agent"''. However, in the "[[Marvel One-Shots]]", Coulson is given ''"a chance to stand in his own spotlight for once"'', when the character is put in a position where there is an imminent threat and no superheroes around. The decision to give more focus to Coulson was ''"a natural"'' for "Marvel One-Shot" co-producer [[Brad Winderbaum]].
*Gregg has stated, ''"I think of Agent Coulson, after all these years, as a guy with a full life. I think every day he's somewhere doing something for S.H.I.E.L.D., and yet I don't always know what that is... There's always a different twist. In this one he gets to show more of his wisecracking wit, and in this one he's a little bit more of a badass."''
*Despite Coulson being called ''"the most recognizable face in the [[Marvel Comics (publisher)]] movie universe"'', he is depicted as an "{{WPS|Everyman}}" in a universe full of superheroes – "the glue that binds" the characters together. In ''Thor'', Coulson complains that Tony Stark ''"never tells [him] anything."'' In an interview with WNBC, Gregg explained his portrayal of the character as 'just a guy grumbling about his job "''He's the guy who's tasked - a very disciplined guy in my opinion who possesses secrets that would turn your hair white - but at the same time he's tasked with handling these kind of diva superheroes, you know? Oh, really, Asgard? Dude, just get in the car''".<ref>[https://www.nbcmiami.com/blogs/popcornbiz/Clark-Gregg--129073283.html Clark Gregg: Marvel Movies' Man of Mystery]</ref>
*There were considerations to bring back Agent Coulson in ''[[Iron Man 3]]'', ''[[Thor: The Dark World]]'' or ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]''.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20130929173225/http://www.craveonline.com/film/articles/173736-clark-gregg-on-the-avengers-marvel-one-shots-iron-man-3-and-more Clark Gregg on ‘The Avengers,’ ‘Marvel One-Shots,’ ‘Iron Man 3′ and More!]</ref> However, Coulson wasn't slated to appear in any of these films.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20131011213515/http://www.comingsoon.net/news/movienews.php?id=106835 Agent Coulson Will Not Appear in Avengers: Age of Ultron]</ref> When asked about the matter, [[Joss Whedon]] asserted that "''As far as the fiction of the movies, Coulson is dead,''"<ref>[https://www.webcitation.org/6fzMFdx73?url=http://mentalfloss.com/uk/movies/28527/qa-joss-whedon-on-super-heroes-the-pop-culture-mainstream Q&A: Joss Whedon on Super Heroes, the Pop Culture Mainstream]</ref> elaborating that "''generally I [Whedon] feel like the ''S.H.I.E.L.D.'' audience and ''The Avengers'' audiences are not actually the same group, necessarily,''" and so the films would have to explain Coulson's resurrection again for the film-only audience if he were to be reintroduced.<ref>[https://screencrush.com/joss-whedon-agents-of-shield-coulson-marvel-tv/ JOSS WHEDON DEFENDS ‘AGENTS OF S.H.I.E.L.D.’ COMMENTS, SAYS MARVEL TV GETS ‘LEFTOVERS’]</ref>
**When asked if there were any plans for the [[Avengers]] to find out that Coulson had been resurrected in ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]'', [[Jeph Loeb]] hinted that there were plans for it in the future.<ref>[https://ew.com/article/2015/05/05/agents-shield-age-ultron-crossover/ Agents of SHIELD: Inside the tie-in to Avengers: Age of Ultron]</ref>
**In the ''[[Loki (TV series)|Loki]]'' series premiere ''[[Glorious Purpose (Loki Season One)|Glorious Purpose]]'', no mentions of Coulson's resurrection are made when [[Mobius M. Mobius]] shows [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] clips of his actions throughout his life. When asked if he toyed with revealing that Coulson was revived afterwards, [[Michael Waldron]] said: "''No, look, that is one other tendril of the [[multiverse]], perhaps. I think just seeing mention of Coulson again, the very fact that it raises those questions, is exciting''".<ref>[https://www.fandom.com/articles/loki-tom-hiddleston-mcu-hero-betrayal-mobius Tom Hiddleston on Loki’s Biggest Betrayals and Most Heroic Moments]</ref>
*[[Andy Dylan]], [[Vinny O'Brien]], [[Dane Farwell]], [[G. Grant Jewett]], [[Casey Adams]], [[Denney Pierce]] and [[Brian Avery]] were stunt doubles for [[Clark Gregg]] in the role of Phil Coulson.
*According to Clark Gregg, the 'J' in the 'Philip J. Coulson' stands for Jaekwon.<ref>[https://twitter.com/clarkgregg/status/210611311401369600 Clark Gregg on Twitter - June 7, 2012]</ref>

